[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_3nuwp")
reagent_id = "HNO3"
title = "Nitric acid"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]HNO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]63 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Liquid[/cell]
[cell]Type:[/cell][cell]Strong acid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
H₂O + 3NO₂ → 2HNO₃ + NO
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Highly corrosive and very reactive.
• A strong oxidizing agent.
• Reacts with many metals, bases, and compounds.
[b]Where nitric acid is found[/b]
• Produced industrially from ammonia (NH₃).
• Used widely in chemical industry.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of fertilizers (nitrates).
• Used to make explosives and chemicals.
• Metal cleaning and processing.
[b]Safety[/b]
Very corrosive — can cause severe burns to skin and eyes.
Vapors are harmful to breathe."
